%F A003125 A(m, p) = 0 for m < 0 or p < 0. A(0, 0) = 0. A(1, 0) = -1. A(0, 1) = 1. Otherwise, A(m, p) = A(m - 1, p) + A(m, p - 1).
%F A003125 B(m, p) = 0 for m < 0 or p < 0. Otherwise, B(m, p) = max{0, A(m, p) + B(m - 1, p) + B(m, p - 1)}.
%F A003125 a(n) = B(n, n + 2). - _Sean A. Irvine_, Feb 02 2015
